The paper focuses on developing a system for interactive visual data exploration, which is a common topic in human-computer interaction (HCI) research. The system also involves performance optimization techniques, which could fall under database (DB) and information retrieval (IR) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a suite of techniques for achieving fast response times, which could be related to data structures (DS) and graphics (GR) categories.
